<item>
            <title>[LU-6487] Current working combination of lustre and Mellanox OFED</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6487</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I am trying to set up Lustre to use InfiniBand using Mellanox cards.&lt;br/&gt;
This is just for a lab environment.&lt;br/&gt;
Is there a recommendation for a combination of versions of Centos, Lustre, and Mellanox OFED?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using Centos 6.6 Luster 2.7 and Mellanox OFED 2.4 running &lt;br/&gt;
./configure --with-o2ib=/usr/src/mlnx-ofa_kernel-2.4/&lt;br/&gt;
I get &lt;br/&gt;
configure: error: can&apos;t compile with OpenIB gen2 headers under /usr/src/ofa_kernel-2.4&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cb&lt;/p&gt;</description>
